      text: |
        <p><strong><span style="color:$primary;">Step 4</span></strong></p>
        <p>Output</p>
        <p>Validation</p>
  - elementId: details
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 190, 1160, 490]
    content:
      fontSize: 16
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Step 1 — Metrics Computation:</strong> For each of the 42 grain-horizon combinations, the system computes deltas (forecast vs actual), permutation importance scores for feature attribution, and anomaly flags including Z-score deviation, coverage rate (p10–p90), and structural shift detection (train/test mean ratio > 2×).</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Step 2 — Prompt Engineering:</strong> Structured 4-sentence prompts enforce explicit constraints: (1) cite specific numbers from the forecast, (2) name the top two drivers by permutation importance, (3) flag anomalies with cautious language, (4) recommend a concrete next step. Prompts include grain name, horizon, forecast values, actuals, and all computed metrics.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Step 3 — LLM Inference:</strong> NVIDIA API (google/gemma-2-2b-it) via OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Temperature 0.7 for controlled creativity. Each grain-horizon combination receives an independent prompt. Total output: 42 structured JSON explanations with business narratives.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Step 4 — Output Validation:</strong> Every narrative is checked for number grounding (all cited figures must match input data), causal caution (must use "associated with," "correlated with," or "suggests" — never "caused by"), and actionability (must include a specific next-step recommendation).</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Caution Language Rules:</strong></p>
        <p>• All claims use associative language: "associated with," "correlated with," "suggests"</p>
        <p>• Causation is never asserted; relationships are framed as statistical associations</p>
        <p>• Anomaly flags include investigation recommendations, not definitive diagnoses</p>
        <p>• All numbers are grounded in actual forecast data to prevent hallucination</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Stage 6 AI Explanation, NVIDIA API (google/gemma-2-2b-it)</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>10</p>
